President Obama and Mrs. Obama extend their wishes and prayers to Nelson Mandela on his 95th birthday. They were deeply moved by their visit to Mandela's former cell on Robben Island and draw inspiration from his moral courage, kindness, and humility. They encourage people to honor Mandela through acts of service and to follow his example of justice, equality, and freedom. They hope Mandela's commitment to service and human dignity will continue to inspire future generations.